data.title: Zeta Chapter
data.text:
Alumni Win Football 14-13!

The Actives got off to an early 13-0 lead, but a missed extra point would prove costly. Jon Frost & Bryan Goers pulled double duty at QB for the Alumni and Tony DiFatta took the snaps for the Actives. In the closing minutes of the game, the Alumni powered down the field (thanks in part to multiple penalties from a jumpy O-Lineman on the Active team) down 13-7. With less than 2 minutes on the clock, Jason Rottler made a game winning diving catch in the end zone smacking his head on the ground causing a concussion (although he didnt realize it at the time). The actives had 1 last drive, and they got close to winning, but an already concussed Rottler made the game ending interception.

The Century Club

The Century Club is a life-time commitment to donate $100 a year to a savings account managed by Delta-Zeta's Housing Corporation. The funds directly benefit Delta-Zeta Chapter by providing: Scholarships, Leadership training, repairs to the Chapter House, funding for a new Chapter house. Since the program's inception in 2003, we have over 40 members.

To join or make your yearly donation, you can mail your check and membership form to:

Sigma Pi Housing Management Corporation

Attn: Tim Schonhoff

1410 Burning Tree Lane, Florissant, MO 63033
